AB  - Competition is increasingly global. However, location still matters: often\nfirms cluster in the same geographic areas in order to exploit locational\nexternalities and improve their competitiveness. This paper analyzes how\nItalian firms’ performance, proxied by their propensity to export, depends\nboth on geographical and institutional context and on individual characteristics.\nUsing a multilevel approach, we estimate and distinguish the effect\nof individual (firm level) and context (province level) variables on the performance of internationalized Italian firms. We show that both firms and province heterogeneity shape the results.
