AB  - We investigate born global firms, companies that expand rapidly into foreign markets from or near their founding, to see how they are able to succeed despite limited resources and experience. We highlight the roles of knowledge and capabilities for early internationalization and success in international markets. Results from a survey-based study suggest born global firms have a distinctive mix of orientations and strategies that allow them to succeed in international markets. Specifically, research revealed that possession of an international entrepreneurial orientation, a focus and/or differentiation strategy, and marketing capabilities are important antecedent factors in the international performance of born global firms. These results are discussed.
