AB  - In order to evaluate the influence of corporate attributes on information quality in financial reports issued by Brazilian public firms, we conducted a descriptive study on 407 firms traded on B3, submitting the collected data to statistical analysis. Three major attributes were considered: corporate governance, internationalization and corporate performance. Information quality was proxied by republication of financial reports, based on the assumption that information quality was lower in the original reports. When analyzed from this perspective, corporate attributes could not be shown to influence information quality. However, a separate analysis of the variables contained in the governance index revealed a positive influence of ‘disclosure policy’ on republication. Likewise, one of the variables of internationalization (number of stock exchanges the firm is traded on) had a positive impact on republication. Corporate performance had no influence on information quality.
