AB  - Against the backdrop of global automotive electrification, Southeast Asia (ASEAN) has emerged as a core growth market for electric vehicles (EVs). This paper conducts a management-oriented systematic review to explore the internationalization strategies and competitive dynamics of EV firms in ASEAN. Grounded in the OLI paradigm, institutional theory and the Uppsala model, it synthesizes key internationalization approaches including regional integration, localization and strategic partnerships, and analyzes competitive interactions between global and local players driven by cost advantages, technological disruption, policy instruments and value chain restructuring. The review identifies critical research gaps including insufficient cross-national comparative research, limited long-term performance analysis, and inadequate attention to digitalization and institutional entrepreneurship. It further proposes a future research agenda to advance international business theories and managerial practices.
