AB  - Excellent operational performance is critical to firms. Financial internationalization and liberalization are imperative under the World Trade Organization (WTO). To enhance operational performance, this study conducted a questionnaire survey of employees of life insurers, with the focus on balanced scorecard (BSC) aspects, as variables. Unlike traditional methods of analysis, this study combined data envelopment analysis (DEA) and a regression model to evaluate performance and determine improvement strategies. Empirical results suggest that “the net written premium to earning ratio” and “mechanism of customer repurchase” significantly affect operational performance. Results are contrasted with those from previous studies, and managerial implications are proposed for reference.	 	Key words: Operational performance, balanced scorecard (BSC), data envelopment analysis (DEA), improvement strategies.
